'''Thomas P. Vitale''' is Executive [[Vice president|Vice President]] of Programming & [[Sci Fi Pictures original films|Original Movies]] for [[Syfy]] and Chiller, and is responsible for the acquisition and scheduling of all programming, as well as the development and commissioning of original movies and specials, for both networks.<ref>[http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/38143/who-wants-be-a-syfy-filmmaker Who Wants to be a Syfy Filmmaker?]</ref>
==Biography== He started working for the network in March 1993.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scifi.com/transcripts/2001/thomas_vitale.html|title=SCIFI.COM Chat Transcript: Thomas Vitale, October 11, 2001|date=2001-10-11|work=SciFi.com|accessdate=2006-08-12 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20060315054942/http://www.scifi.com/transcripts/2001/thomas_vitale.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2006-03-15}}</ref>
Vitale has worked for [[television]] since 1987 with [[stint]]s at [[Viacom]], in program syndication, and [[NBC]].<ref>[http://www.farscapeworld.com/interviews/interviews.php?id=scifitom FarscapeWorld.com - Interview with a SciFi Programming Executive]</ref> In 1999, Vitale co-produced an [[Off-Off-Broadway]] play, ''Dyslexic Heart''.<ref>[http://www.animationmagazine.net/article.php?article_id=2510 Thomas Vitale, Buyer for SCI FI Channel: Not Looking for Your Dad's Space Fiction]</ref> A graduate of [[Williams College]], Vitale sat on the board of the [[Williams Club]] for nearly 10 years, and remains active in Williams alumni activity. He also served as President of Fieri Manhattan, and was the NYS Vice President of [[Fieri|Fieri National]], an [[Italian-American]] service, cultural and charitable organization.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.phobosweb.com/books/empire/jury/vitale.html|title=Thomas Vitale Bio|date=2004-08-22|work=Phobos Entertainment|accessdate=2006-08-18 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20060510193015/http://www.phobosweb.com/books/empire/jury/vitale.html <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2006-05-10}}</ref>
